        "description": "The choice of turbulence model, constitutive relations, and hemolysis damage model are justified against available literature and experimental evidence for the relevant flow regime and device type."
      },
      "rationale": "The SST k-ω turbulence model is selected based on its documented performance for internal rotating flows in centrifugal pumps (Celik et al. 2008, Taskin et al. 2012). The Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model is the regulatory standard for CFD-based hemolysis prediction. An explicitly-flagged epistemic uncertainty exists: the Giersiepen model coefficients carry inter-laboratory variability of approximately ±20%, producing the ±18% wide uncertainty band on RH documented in ValidationResult hemolysis-index-comparison. This gap is fully acknowledged; the model-form achievedLevel is conservatively held at 2 (not 3) to reflect this known limitation. The safety margin (all RH < 0.82 vs. threshold 1.0) and physical testing corroboration at 3 operating points provide sufficient confidence for MRL 2 acceptance."
